                    <li>There are 79.5 million people around the world who have been forcibly displaced—the highest figure ever recorded!</li>
                    <li>About 1% of the world's population is displaced.</li>
                    <li>50% of the world's refugees are children.</li>
                    <li>Having fled the danger of their home countries and languishing in limbo for months--or many times years--refugees enter the United States with next to nothing.</li>
